text: Angasyak () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Angasyakovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,850 as of 2010. There are 20 streets. == Geography == It is located 18 km from Dyurtyuli, 67 km from Yanaul. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Angasyak
